      <biogHist id="md5-d6134e59926494c82f25e288806ff091">
        <p>Lawyer, Civil Servant, Author, [1865]-1946.  A witness to the driving of the last spike for the trans-Canada railway line, Duncan Stuart was a major with the Royal Canadian Regiment of Infantry during the Boer War from 1899 to 1900. He was then employed as a civil servant for Great Britain in the Transvaal, 1900-1908.  Returning to Canada, he studied soil and water management and wrote several books that proposed solutions to problems of soil erosion in Western Canada during the 1930s.</p>
      </biogHist>
